cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with few-shot classification, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on vision classification datasets, which suggests that it could also fall under "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using unlabelled inputs, which could be considered as unsupervised learning, and hence it could also fall under "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). The use of graph convolutions suggests that it could also fall under "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). Finally, the use of state-of-the-art approaches and the focus on accuracy suggests that it could also fall under "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE).
